{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17621329","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17621329"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:53:31+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:53:31+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16707"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16707","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16707"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9398"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75870"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9398","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9398"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16707"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61383"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"6"},{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"35"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1531"},{"type":"tags","id":"3300"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"10387"},{"type":"tags","id":"10438"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22245"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22250"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75870","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75870"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 65-year-old woman is referred to the Speech Pathology clinic for assessment of progressive word-finding difficulties over the past six months. She has a history of hypertension and type 2 diabetes mellitus. Her medications include Metformin and Perindopril. She is a retired teacher who lives independently.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Her Mini-Mental State Examination score is 24/30 (24-30).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is most appropriate to check before proceeding with formal language assessment?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Recent hearing assessment","Formal IQ testing","Psychiatric review","Neuroimaging","Family history"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EBefore conducting formal language assessment, it is essential to ensure that basic sensory functions are intact and not contributing to communication difficulties. A \u003Cstrong\u003Erecent hearing assessment\u003C/strong\u003E is crucial as hearing impairment can significantly impact language assessment results.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFormal IQ testing\u003C/strong\u003E is time-consuming and unnecessary for initial language assessment. Brief cognitive screening tools like the Mini-Mental State Examination are usually sufficient.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile \u003Cstrong\u003Epsychiatric review\u003C/strong\u003E may be relevant in some cases, particularly if depression or anxiety are suspected, it is not a prerequisite for language assessment.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENeuroimaging\u003C/strong\u003E may be indicated based on the results of language assessment but is not required before initial evaluation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFamily history\u003C/strong\u003E, while potentially helpful in understanding genetic risk factors, is not essential before proceeding with language assessment.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther important considerations before language assessment include vision screening, cultural and linguistic background, and educational history. The goal is to ensure that any identified language deficits are not due to correctable sensory impairments or other confounding factors.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Hearing, vision, and cognitive function must be assessed before formal language assessment.","Language assessment requires consideration of cultural and linguistic background.","Standardised cognitive screening tools are preferred over formal IQ testing as a prerequisite for language assessment."],"references":["Parente MAMP, Baradel RR, Fonseca RP, Pereira N, Carthery-Goulart MT. Evolution of language assessment in patients with acquired neurological disorders in Brazil. Dement Neuropsychol. 2014 Jul-Sep;8(3):196-206. doi: 10.1590/S1980-57642014DN83000002. PMID: 29213904; PMCID: PMC5619395.","Kujawa K, Zurek G, Kwiatkowska A, Olejniczak R, \u017burek A. Assessment of Language Functions in Patients With Disorders of Consciousness Using an Alternative Communication Tool. Front Neurol. 2021 Jul 20;12:684362. doi: 10.3389/fneur.2021.684362. PMID: 34354661; PMCID: PMC8329337.","Tippett DC, Niparko JK, Hillis AE. Aphasia: Current Concepts in Theory and Practice. J Neurol Transl Neurosci. 2014 Jan;2(1):1042. PMID: 24904925; PMCID: PMC4041294","Richardson JD, Dalton SG. Assessment of language impairment and function. Handb Clin Neurol. 2022;185:175-193. doi: 10.1016/B978-0-12-823384-9.00009-8. PMID: 35078598; PMCID: PMC11363586."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61383"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16707"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61383","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61383"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-01T05:40:18+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-01T05:40:18+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9398"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75870"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"6","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/6"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc75","name":"Geriatrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,